to do right by my client.

35:31.390 --> 35:34.175
He says that he's
willing to testify if needed.

35:35.220 --> 35:37.570
Ms. Palmer, how do
the people wish to proceed?

35:37.613 --> 35:39.093
Your Honor.

35:46.318 --> 35:49.843
This new evidence corroborates
Damien Owens'’ affidavit.

35:49.886 --> 35:51.366
The people are
no longer confident

35:51.410 --> 35:54.108
we could prove the case
beyond reasonable doubt.

35:54.152 --> 35:55.240
Therefore...

35:55.762 --> 35:57.807
we are
withdrawing our opposition

35:57.851 --> 36:00.070
to the habeas petition and...

36:00.332 --> 36:03.813
agree the conviction
should be vacated.

36:04.249 --> 36:05.859
If the people are no longer

36:05.902 --> 36:07.208
contesting the writ,
then this court

36:07.252 --> 36:10.342
will return this
case to the Court of Appeal

36:10.385 --> 36:12.431
and recommend
that the writ be granted.

36:12.474 --> 36:13.954
Mr. Mack.

36:16.391 --> 36:19.829
You are released
on your own recognizance.

36:20.569 --> 36:21.701
Thank you, Your Honor.

36:22.267 --> 36:24.399
Mr. Mack,
I would like to apologize

36:25.052 --> 36:26.793
on behalf of the court.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.317
Today is a bittersweet moment.

36:29.361 --> 36:32.712
There is much
to celebrate in that justice

36:32.755 --> 36:34.409
has finally been served.

36:34.453 --> 36:38.326
But there's so much
disappointment and sadness

36:38.370 --> 36:39.980
that it took so long.

36:42.548 --> 36:43.940
This court is adjourned.

36:45.768 --> 36:47.248
Baby, you did it!

36:47.292 --> 36:49.859
You're free daddy.

